Adult.description: White-breasted Nuthatches are larger with a black hood and a white face, including white all the way around the eye, instead of the Pygmy Nuthatch’s crisp brown cap.
Red-breasted Nuthatches have a prominent white stripe over the eye and reddish-cinnamon underparts, two features Pygmy Nuthatches don't have.

Adult/immature.description: The Brown-headed Nuthatch of the southeastern U.S. looks very similar to the Pygmy Nuthatch, but their ranges don’t overlap.

Male (Pacific).description: Bushtits have much longer tails than the stubby-tailed Pygmy Nuthatch. Bushtits don't climb up and down tree trunks the way Pygmy Nuthatches do.
